events.body: I want to transfer money from my account

To transfer money from your DDD Bank Savings Account, you can follow these steps:
1. Click on the DDD Savings Account tile on the home screen, or select Bank from the bottom menu and then choose DDD Savings Accounts.
2. Select Transfers, and then choose Send Money.
3. If your payee is already added, you can select their name from the list and proceed. If not, add the details (account number, beneficiary name, IFSC Code) of the payee.
4. Enter the OTP sent to your registered mobile number to verify the payee.
5. Once the payee details are verified, select Send Money, enter the amount, and click Authorize Transfer.
6. Enter the OTP sent to your registered mobile number to transfer the amount.

For quick/instant fund transfer without any cooling periods, you can use any UPI apps, such as Google Pay or PhonePe. Simply link your DDD Bank Savings Account with the UPI app and then transfer the money from the app.

If you have any other questions or need further assistance, feel free to ask!

events.body: What is tcs charges

The Tax Collected at Source (TCS) is applicable to international transactions made with your DDD Bank Global card. If your overall international spending in a financial year (FY) is less than Rs 5 Lakhs, no TCS is charged to you. However, if the international spending exceeds Rs 5 Lakhs, a 20% TCS is deducted upfront for all international transactions. The TCS deducted is reversed within 2 hours if your overall international spending in an FY is greater than Rs 5 Lakhs but less than 7 lakh. In cases where the spending crosses the 7 lakh limit, the 20% TCS applies only to the amount spent beyond the 7 lakh limit, and you can claim a TCS refund for this amount while filing your Income Tax Returns (ITR).
